The evidence with the title 'How many Mexicans actually cross the border illegally? ' says Oct 9, 2016  ... A new study says the number has been reduced to 170000 in 2015 , one-tenth what it was in 2005 .  ... What 's more, the probability that an an illegal immigrant from Mexico will be caught by the Border Patrol has risen from about 36 percent in 2005 to about 54 percent in 2015 , the DHS report estimates . 
